att: English: "No Honest Man Need Fear Cartoons" By Homer C. Davenport. "No Honest Man Need Fear Cartoons." Behind the figure of Senator Platt is the visage of Boss Tweed, one of the principals from an earlier generation of political corruption, who was in part brought down by Davenport's inspiration, Thomas Nast, who had attacked the Tammany Hall political machine that controlled New York City’s municipal government. Source Image from the book "Cartoons" by H.C. Davenport. The De Witt Publishing House, NYC 1898. Scanned and processed from the book owned by the contributor.
